==Russian==
[[Category:Russian nouns]]
===Etymology===
Originally, '''друг''' was the predicative (short) form of [[другой]] (“another”). It is related to [[второй]] ("second”) < [[OCS]] <u>въторъ</u> (“other”, "second”) < [[PIE]] *<u>wi-tero</u>- (“more apart”) < PIE base *<u>wi</u>- (“separation”) + [[comparative]] suffix *-<u>tero</u>- (“-er”).

===Noun===
'''друг''' (drug) {{m}}, [[друзья]] (druz’já) {{p}}

# [[friend]]
#:*{{RUchar|[[близкий|бли́зкий]] друг}} — ''close friend''
#:*{{RUchar|[[старинный|стари́нный]] друг}} — ''very old friend''
#:*{{RUchar|друг [[дом|до́ма]]}} — ''friend of the family''
#:*{{RUchar|друг [[детство|де́тства]]}} — ''childhood friend''
#''(in pairs)'' [[other]], [[another]]
#:*{{RUchar|друг дру́га}} — ''[[one another]]; [[each other]]''
#:*{{RUchar|друг дру́гу}} — ''to one another; to each other''
#:*{{RUchar|друг на дру́га}} — ''against each other''
#:*{{RUchar|друг от дру́га}} — ''one from another''
#:*{{RUchar|друг у дру́га}} — ''at one another; from one another''
#:*{{RUchar|друг за дру́гом}} — ''one after another; [[in single file]]''
#:*{{RUchar|друг с дру́гом}} — ''with each other''
#:*{{RUchar|друг про́тив дру́га}} — ''face to face; [[vis-à-vis]]''

